A product leak was detected at the manifold connection of MLA 400. The GPHA Mechanical Team attended the site to address the leak. Despite the line being full and opening of the drain valve V-401A, no product was observed flowing into the sump. The product in the Arm was drained at the ship end. It is suspected that the drain valve may be clogged, and a request has been made for the maintenance team to investigate this issue.

Removed the malfunctioning V-401A valve and replaced it with V-201A. Subsequently, V-201A underwent servicing to ensure optimal functionality before being reinstalled onto MLA400. Awaiting for a new valve replacement.
